---
import Base from '../layouts/Base.astro';
import Header from '../components/Header.astro';
import Footer from '../components/Footer.astro';
---

<Base title="Privacy Policy" description="Privacy Policy for Clarissa - your data stays private by design">
  <Header />
  <main class="container legal-page">
    <h1 class="gradient-text">Privacy Policy</h1>
    <p class="last-updated">Last updated: December 12, 2025</p>

    <section>
      <h2>Overview</h2>
      <p>
        Clarissa is designed with privacy as a core principle. The iOS app processes conversations 
        entirely on-device using Apple's Foundation Models when available. The CLI version connects 
        to your configured LLM provider.
      </p>
    </section>

    <section>
      <h2>Data We Don't Collect</h2>
      <p>We do not collect, store, or transmit:</p>
      <ul>
        <li>Your conversations or chat history</li>
        <li>Personal information or identifiers</li>
        <li>Usage analytics or telemetry</li>
        <li>Device information or diagnostics</li>
        <li>Calendar or contacts data</li>
      </ul>
    </section>

    <section>
      <h2>On-Device Processing (iOS)</h2>
      <p>
        On iOS 26+ devices with Apple Intelligence enabled, Clarissa uses Apple's Foundation Models 
        for AI processing. All conversations are processed locally on your device and never leave it.
      </p>
      <p>
        Your calendar events and contacts are accessed only when you explicitly use those features, 
        and this data is processed entirely on-device.
      </p>
    </section>

    <section>
      <h2>Optional Cloud Providers</h2>
      <p>
        If you choose to configure an external LLM provider (such as OpenRouter), your conversations 
        will be sent to that provider's servers. In this case:
      </p>
      <ul>
        <li>You provide your own API key directly to the provider</li>
        <li>We do not have access to your API key or conversations</li>
        <li>The provider's privacy policy applies to data sent to their servers</li>
      </ul>
      <p>
        We recommend reviewing your chosen provider's privacy policy:
      </p>
      <ul>
        <li><a href="https://openrouter.ai/privacy" target="_blank" rel="noopener">OpenRouter Privacy Policy</a></li>
        <li><a href="https://openai.com/privacy" target="_blank" rel="noopener">OpenAI Privacy Policy</a></li>
        <li><a href="https://www.anthropic.com/privacy" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Anthropic Privacy Policy</a></li>
      </ul>
    </section>

    <section>
      <h2>Local Storage</h2>
      <p>
        Clarissa stores the following data locally on your device:
      </p>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>Session history</strong> — Your conversation history for session continuity</li>
        <li><strong>Long-term memories</strong> — Facts you explicitly ask Clarissa to remember</li>
        <li><strong>Settings</strong> — Your app preferences and configuration</li>
        <li><strong>API keys</strong> — Stored securely in the system keychain (iOS) or config file (CLI)</li>
      </ul>
      <p>
        This data remains on your device and is not transmitted to us or any third party.
      </p>
    </section>

    <section>
      <h2>Open Source</h2>
      <p>
        Clarissa is open source. You can review the complete source code to verify our privacy practices:
      </p>
      <p>
        <a href="https://github.com/cameronrye/clarissa" target="_blank" rel="noopener">
          github.com/cameronrye/clarissa
        </a>
      </p>
    </section>

    <section>
      <h2>Contact</h2>
      <p>
        If you have questions about this privacy policy, please contact:
      </p>
      <p>
        <strong>Cameron Rye</strong><br />
        <a href="mailto:cameron@rye.dev">cameron@rye.dev</a>
      </p>
    </section>
  </main>
  <Footer />
</Base>

<style>
  .legal-page {
    max-width: 800px;
    padding: 3rem 1.5rem;
  }

  h1 {
    font-size: 2.5rem;
    margin-bottom: 0.5rem;
  }

  .last-updated {
    color: var(--color-text-muted);
    font-size: 0.875rem;
    margin-bottom: 3rem;
  }

  section {
    margin-bottom: 2.5rem;
  }

  h2 {
    font-size: 1.25rem;
    margin-bottom: 1rem;
    color: var(--color-text);
  }

  p, li {
    color: var(--color-text-muted);
    line-height: 1.7;
    margin-bottom: 1rem;
  }

  ul {
    padding-left: 1.5rem;
    margin-bottom: 1rem;
  }

  li {
    margin-bottom: 0.5rem;
  }

  a {
    color: var(--color-cyan);
  }

  a:hover {
    text-decoration: underline;
  }
</style>

